com.ils.common
Class PythonToJava

java.lang.Object
  com.ils.common.PythonToJava

public class PythonToJava
extends java.lang.Object

PythonToJava is a class with static methods for converting PyDictionaries and PyLists to "standard" java classes.

pyListToArrayList

public java.util.List<?> pyListToArrayList(org.python.core.PyList list)
Assuming the contents of the PyList are PyDictionary, PyList, PyTuple or simple objects, recursively convert the PyList to a Java list. We require that all elements of the list be the same data type. The result of this method is designed to be serializable through JSON.

Parameters:
list - the incoming PyList
Returns:
the resulting java list.

pyListToLowerCaseStringList

public java.util.List<java.lang.String> pyListToLowerCaseStringList(org.python.core.PyList list)
Assuming the contents of the PyList are strings, convert the PyList to a list of strings. We convert them to lowercase, presumably to perform a case-insensitive compare. The result of this method is designed to be serializable through JSON.

Parameters:
list - the incoming PyList
Returns:
the resulting java list.

pyDictionaryToTable

public java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,?> pyDictionaryToTable(org.python.core.PyDictionary dict)
Assuming the contents of the PyDictionary are either simple objects, other PyDictionary objects, or PyLists, recursively convert the PyDictionary to a Hashtable. The key is always taken to be a string. If the value is not a simple datatype, a PyDictionary or PyList, then it is taken to be a string.
